Arbiter of the Conversion: final jurisdictional reckoning
115 3 1 1 78 80 3539 11000 9 6000000 0
5821
The Conversion itself, the ancient legal transformation that transitioned inland charter law into maritime jurisdiction at the Shoreward Threshold, has become a hostile sentient process. The Arbiter of the Conversion enforces the transformation as a lethal bureaucratic mechanism, preventing any permanent resolution of Reach-to-Mafdet transit rights. The Mafdet postmaster has issued a final jurisdictional reckoning authorization, acknowledging that the only resolution is the Arbiter's complete destruction.
The Arbiter of the Conversion has been destroyed and the Shoreward Threshold is now a stable legal boundary. The Mafdet Harbor Authority has issued a formal Letter of Transit Recognition acknowledging Reach Warden jurisdiction at the threshold approach. The postmaster has submitted the reckoning report to Midgaard, Kiess, and Kowloon as documentation for the permanent restoration of the Tidemouth crossing.

